      "writtenOn": "2020-01-09T18:54:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I would note that the opposing groups of properties are\n  * data_stream (which contains its own content_type)\n  * (fetch_url, content_type)\n\nOtherwise multiple artifacts could point to the same data_stream with different content types, which would be weird.\n\nAlso for GCS, doesn\u0027t GCS allow you to set the content type directly already?  (https://cloud.google.com/storage/docs/gsutil/addlhelp/WorkingWithObjectMetadata)\n\nIf content_type is just used as a hint for indexing to rdb, maybe it could be reduced to \"index_as\u003dTEXT\" or something like that, and just supplied in conjunction with fetch_url (assuming we want rdb to follow fetch_url via a realm-scoped account and consume that data for indexing). If rdb isn\u0027t going to follow fetch_url itself, then I think content_type probably can just be dropped, and then data_stream would carry its own content_type and index_as flags.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 32,
        "startChar": 14,
